article.headline: CCSU 92, Hartford 58
article.story: NEW BRITAIN, Conn. -- Kyle Vinales scored 25 points, Robby Ptacek added 24 and Ken Horton chipped in 20 for Central Connecticut State in a 92-58 rout of winless Hartford on Saturday. The Blue Devils (3-2) were hot from beyond the arc, knocking down 11 of 17 shots (64.7 percent) in the win. Vinales was 4 of 6 from long range, Ptacek 2 of 4 and Horton 1 of 2. Adonis Burbage scored nine of his 13 points from 3-point range, going a perfect 3 of 3. The Hawks shot just 4 of 15 (26.7 percent) from long range. Hartford had an early 6-2 advantage but Ptacek connected on CCSU's first 3-pointer of the game to start a 32-5 run that he also capped, knocking down a jumper. The Blue Devils never trailed again. Nate Sikma led Hartford (0-6) with 11 points.
